      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">詩經·頌·魯頌·003.8</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">泮水.8</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>翩彼飛鴞，集于泮林。食我桑黮，懷我好音。
憬彼淮夷，來獻其琛。元龜象齒，大賂南金。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>8. They come flying on the wing, those owls,
And settle on the trees about the college;
They eat the fruit of our mulberry trees,
And salute us with fine notes.
So awakened shall be those tribes of the Hwâi.
They will come presenting their precious things,
Their large tortoises, and their elephants' teeth,
And great contributions of the southern metals.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
